# HearMed Portal — Codespace Rules
# These rules are enforced by the AI assistant when writing code for this project.

## CRITICAL: No WordPress Auth Dependencies

This project uses PortalAuth (core/class-portal-auth.php) for ALL authentication.
WordPress auth functions are BANNED in module and admin code.

### BANNED functions — NEVER use these in modules/, admin/, or includes/:
- `get_current_user_id()` → Use `PortalAuth::staff_id()` instead
- `current_user_can()` → Use `PortalAuth::is_logged_in()` or `PortalAuth::is_admin()` instead
- `is_user_logged_in()` → Use `PortalAuth::is_logged_in()` instead
- `wp_get_current_user()` → Use `PortalAuth::current_user()` instead
- `update_user_meta()` with user IDs → Use `HearMed_DB` to write to PG instead
- `get_user_meta()` with user IDs → Query PG staff/settings tables instead

### EXCEPTIONS (these files MAY use WP auth):
- mu-plugins/disable-wp-login.php (runs before plugin, needs WP)
- core/class-hearmed-router.php bridge_wp_login() method ONLY
- core/class-portal-auth.php resolve_legacy() method ONLY
- migrations/ (one-time scripts)

### Auth quick reference:
- Get staff ID: `PortalAuth::staff_id()` → int
- Get staff object: `PortalAuth::current_user()` → object with id, first_name, last_name, email, role
- Check logged in: `PortalAuth::is_logged_in()` → bool
- Check admin: `PortalAuth::is_admin()` → bool
- Get WP user ID (rare): `PortalAuth::wp_user_id()` → int

### Nonce standard:
- Always use 'hm_nonce' as the nonce action name
- Create: `wp_create_nonce('hm_nonce')`
- Verify: `check_ajax_referer('hm_nonce', 'nonce')`
- NEVER use 'hearmed_nonce'

### AJAX handler registration:
- Each module registers its OWN handlers at file level
- NEVER register handlers in class-hearmed-ajax.php (it's a helper class only)
- NEVER register the same action name in two different files
- Action names must be globally unique

### Database:
- All business data is in PostgreSQL (hearmed_core, hearmed_reference, hearmed_admin schemas)
- Use HearMed_DB class for all queries
- WordPress MySQL (wp_options, wp_users, wp_posts) is ONLY for WordPress internals
- NEVER store business data in wp_options or wp_usermeta
